Interface Data.DataReplace

  • Enclosing class:
    Data<DATATYPE extends Data<DATATYPE>>

    public static interface Data.DataReplace
    This interface is used as the argument for the replace() method. It can be used to replace or alter lines in the output.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String replace(java.lang.String input)
      This method is used to alter the lines in the data array.

    • Method Detail

      • replace

        java.lang.String replace(java.lang.String input)
        This method is used to alter the lines in the data array. Each line is parsed to this method, and whatever is returned will replace the current line.
        Parameters:
        input - One line of the data array
